  "id": "02-where-range-operators",
  "title": "MongoDB-style operators (`$gte`) silently ignored; bare operators (`gte`) honored",
  "hypothesis": "Public docs describe `where` only as type \"any\" with no operator examples. We expected MongoDB-style `$gte` (the convention the rest of the `where` shape suggests). The API silently drops `$gte` and returns an unfiltered result, but it does honor the bare `gte` form. Both behaviors are undocumented.",
  "verdict": "CONFIRMED_BUG",
  "summary": "`$gte` is silently dropped (filtered total 5725 = baseline 5725); bare `gte` correctly returns 0 rows for a far-future date. Doc page describes `where` only as type \"any\" with no examples, so partners can't tell which syntax is right.",
